                                     },
                                     {
                                         "text":  "<p><h3>Surface Coordinates</h3>The figure in this section shows the intersection of the <b>Equator parallel</b> and the <i>Greenwich Meridian</i>, marked as point <b>O</b>. This serves as the reference point for all measurements of latitude and longitude.</p>",
                                         "source":  [

                                                    ],
                                         "date_time":  null,
                                         "isTable":  false,
                                         "imgdesc":  "",
                                         "format":  "html",
                                         "PostMention":  ""
                                     },
                                     {
                                         "text":  "<h4>The origin</h4>To determine our position on Earth's surface, we initially use the angular coordinates theta (<b>θ</b>) and phi (<b>ϕ</b>). However, in everyday terminology, these coordinates are known by different names: theta (<b>θ</b>) corresponds to <b>longitude</b>, and phi (<b>ϕ</b>) is referred to as <b>colatitude</b>. In geographic contexts, we also use a measure called <b>latitude</b> (<b>δ</b>), which indicates position relative to the Equator. The relationship between latitude and colatitude is defined by the formula: ϕ = 90° - δ. This is just one of the simplifications we will explore further",
                                         "source":  [
                                                        {
                                                            "type":  1,
                                                            "uuid":  "006b21c9-6800-4deb-bb3f-a367dd38b703",
                                                            "text":  "NOAA",
                                                            "page":  "Longitude",
                                                            "date_time":  {
                                                                              "type":  "gregory",
                                                                              "year":  "2024",
                                                                              "month":  "06",
                                                                              "day":  "16"
                                                                          }
                                                        },
                                                        {
                                                            "type":  1,
                                                            "uuid":  "72ea1365-bb46-4036-a9e2-7384896e0a28",
                                                            "text":  "NOAA",
                                                            "page":  "Latitude",
                                                            "date_time":  {
                                                                              "type":  "gregory",
                                                                              "year":  "2024",
                                                                              "month":  "06",
                                                                              "day":  "16"
                                                                          }
                                                        },
                                                        {
                                                            "type":  1,
                                                            "uuid":  "98aee156-df44-4def-a664-a7db2131c33d",
                                                            "text":  "Weisstein, Eric W.",
